sources.title: Spies-a-Go-Go (1964) ARCH HALL, JR.
sources.description:
Movie Class by PizzaFLIX: Arch Hall Jr. is an American actor and musician who appeared in six indie films during the 1960s all produced by Nicholas Merriwether, the pseudonym of his father Arch Hall Sr.

Stars: Arch Hall Jr., Michael Terr, Liz Renay
Director: James Landis

In the this wild fiasco of Cold War espionage, an American super agent goes under cover as a Rock 'n' Roll heartthrob to thwart a pair diabolical Soviet spies who plan to wipe out the US population with a radio-active bunny. (a.k.a. The Nasty Rabbit)
